<subSubSection box="[160,842,1130,1189]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,842,1130,1189]" box="[160,285,1130,1155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,842,1130,1189]" box="[160,842,1165,1189]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Latin, ‘longimanus’ refers to the relatively longer male palp.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="478" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,1243,1406]" box="[160,276,1243,1268]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1243,1268]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,1243,1406]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">
Distinguished from known congeners by the distinctive shape of E (thick, stout tip), C (tapering, screw-like tip; 
<figureCitation box="[435,537,1313,1337]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1603,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1572]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[163,1152,142,1572]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Epidius longimanus sp. nov. MNHN 9783 (a–d) and Epidius mahavira sp. nov. MNHN 14,996 (e). (a, e) Male dorsal view. (b) Female, dorsal view. (c) Male palp, proloateral/ventral view. (d) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars: c, d = 0.2 mm; a, e = 1.0 mm; b = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184395/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Figures 5</figureCitation>
(d), 6(a), and 8(c)) and absence of RTA (
<figureCitation box="[974,1076,1313,1337]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1603,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1572]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[163,1152,142,1572]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Epidius longimanus sp. nov. MNHN 9783 (a–d) and Epidius mahavira sp. nov. MNHN 14,996 (e). (a, e) Male dorsal view. (b) Female, dorsal view. (c) Male palp, proloateral/ventral view. (d) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars: c, d = 0.2 mm; a, e = 1.0 mm; b = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184395/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Figures 5</figureCitation>
(d) and 6(a)). Females are distinguished by the globular S, and except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Benjamin, 2017" authorityName="Benjamin" authorityYear="2017" box="[892,985,1347,1372]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="478" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floreni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[892,985,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">E. floreni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[991,1078,1348,1372]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the deeply indented anterior margin of the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[748,843,1382,1406]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1276,1299]" captionTargetBox="[163,1151,143,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-65@12.[163,1152,142,1245]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Epidius longimanus sp. nov. MNHN 9783. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Epigynum, ventral view. (d) vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184397/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(b, c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="480" pageId="10" pageNumber="478" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,1460,1727]" box="[160,294,1460,1485]" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,1460,1727]" lastBlockId="12.[160,1156,1387,1445]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="480" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,224,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Male.</emphasis>
Total length: 4.0; prosoma length: 2.1, width: 1.6. Leg I: femur 3.6, patella 0.9, tibia 3.4, metatarsus 3.3. tarsus 1.7. Prosoma yellow, without prominent markings or conspicuous setae. Opisthosoma light yellow, dorsally with inconspicuous brown spots. ALE = PLE&gt; PME&gt; AME. AER, PER recurved, eyes on brown-coloured protuberances. Chelicerae with 3 and 2 teeth on pro- and retromargin of fang furrow, respectively. Leg formula 1243. Palps as in 
<figureCitation box="[660,766,1669,1693]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1603,1626]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1572]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[163,1152,142,1572]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Epidius longimanus sp. nov. MNHN 9783 (a–d) and Epidius mahavira sp. nov. MNHN 14,996 (e). (a, e) Male dorsal view. (b) Female, dorsal view. (c) Male palp, proloateral/ventral view. (d) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars: c, d = 0.2 mm; a, e = 1.0 mm; b = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184395/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="478">Figures 5</figureCitation>
(d), 6(a), and 8(c), femur and tibia characteristically elongated, femur as long as tibia, furnished with 2 thick long spines and MTr, RTA absent. Bulbus ovoid, conductor with a screw-like tip, MA absent. Embolus stout, tapering.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184395" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5184395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184395/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="479" startId="11.[160,225,1603,1626]" targetBox="[163,1152,142,1572]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1157,1602,1685]" pageId="11" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,250,1603,1626]" pageId="11" pageNumber="479">Figure 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Benjamin, 2017" authorityName="Benjamin" authorityYear="2017" box="[259,445,1602,1625]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longimanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[259,445,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="479">Epidius longimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[452,529,1603,1626]" pageId="11" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
MNHN 9783 (a–d) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Benjamin, 2017" authorityName="Benjamin" authorityYear="2017" box="[763,928,1602,1625]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahavira" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[763,928,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="479">Epidius mahavira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[936,1013,1603,1626]" pageId="11" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
MNHN 14,996 (e). (a, e) Male dorsal view. (b) Female, dorsal view. (c) Male palp, proloateral/ventral view. (d) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars: c, d = 0.2 mm; a, e = 1.0 mm; b = 2.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184397" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5184397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184397/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="480" startId="12.[160,225,1276,1299]" targetBox="[163,1151,143,1233]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[160,1155,1275,1328]" pageId="12" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,250,1276,1299]" pageId="12" pageNumber="480">Figure 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Benjamin, 2017" authorityName="Benjamin" authorityYear="2017" box="[259,445,1275,1298]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longimanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[259,445,1275,1298]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="480">Epidius longimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[452,530,1276,1299]" pageId="12" pageNumber="480" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
MNHN 9783. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Epigynum, ventral view. (d) vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="12.[160,1156,1511,1640]" pageId="12" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1511,1536]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="480">Female.</emphasis>
Total length: 6.0; prosoma length: 2.4, width: 2.1. Leg I: femur 3.6, patella 0.9, tibia 3.2, metatarsus 2.4, tarsus 1.2. In general similar to male. Epigynum without hood, anterior margin deeply indented, dual-chambered S connected by a C-shaped, thickwalled CD (
<figureCitation box="[292,388,1616,1640]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1276,1299]" captionTargetBox="[163,1151,143,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-65@12.[163,1152,142,1245]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Epidius longimanus sp. nov. MNHN 9783. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Epigynum, ventral view. (d) vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184397" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184397/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="480">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(b, c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="481" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,142,271]" box="[160,300,142,167]" pageId="13" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="481">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1156,142,271]" pageId="13" pageNumber="481">
Known only from Kodaikanal and Trichanophilai in 
<collectingCountry box="[723,778,178,202]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="481">India</collectingCountry>
